HEADWORD: perdurantism
<hw>per*dur"ant*ism</hw> <pr>(p⟦etil⟧r*d⟦umac⟧r"⟦ait⟧nt*⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Philosophy)</fld> <def>The philosophical view
considering the fundamental objects of the real world as extended in the
direction of time, so that the objects themselves do not change, though
temporal parts may have different properties. Contrasted to
<contr>endurantism</contr>, a view considering objects to be wholly
present at each instant of time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>perdurantist</ent>⟦br⟧
